task.summary: Default task
Added ability to select items in fridge and then perform searches using them.
Debugged searching for recipes based on items selected in fridge.
Added prompt for if the search query returned no results.
Now saves the url and downloads images of items in the fridge from the web.
Fixed Matt's onAttach issue. Items in fridge also display in alphabetical order.
Fixed low res photo in search issue by changing the layout. Also included a primary color "covered plate" icon to display if there is no image or while it is loading.
Added the new directions link and parsed the link and source title from return JSON.
Saving the images of saved recipes locally instead of requiring an image download each time.
Images of items int eh fridge are now saved locally, fixing the bug of the fridge taking to long to load.
Updating with new drawables.
Created framework for searching bing for images of new ingredients.
You can now add an item to the fridge, including a toast to ask which food group it belongs to and and subsequently navigating to that part of the fridge.
Search box in My Recipes is now functional.
Search box in Search Recipes is now functional. Includes the text in the query to Yummly.
Added an icon to the app. It is just a simple orange person wearing a chef hat.
Homescreen now pulls data from yummly for the recipes of the week.
Edited UniversalImageLoader configuration settings.
Small change to settings.
Search now refines by allergies and diets.
Recipes now parse nutrition information from JSON, store it in the database, and load it into the actual recipe view.
Nutrition is now fully shown in the recipe fragment.
Fixed bug where clicking on a recipes when my recipes is filtered goes to the wrong one.
Minor changes to fridge and ingredient.
Added checkbox and functionality to decide if the user wants to filter by their favorite cuisines. Works perfectly!
Began working on the Bing Image API call.
Built the whole database for fridge and all functionality for it.
Small changes for code readability purposes.
Built the Bing Image Request method. Modified the IngredientSearchAdapter to account for this.
Added more error handling for web requests. Special characters, support for multiple words, etc.
Included radio button for "No Diet" as it was previously impossible no de-select all diets. Also added the saving for "paleo" as it was missed previously, apparently.
Working on optimizing performance of the fridge. Still working on the first item in gridview bug.
App will now not rotate if someone tilts their phone.
All images now display correctly and quickly in fridge and ingredient search.
Added border between items in my recipes.
Fixed issue of leaking database connections to Recipe Database.
Fixed issue of leaking database connections to Fridge Database. No database connections of any type should be leaked now.
Removed excess/dated drawable images, helping memory usage by at least 20%.
